.TH in.stlisten 1M "11 Dec 2007" "SunOS 5.11" "System Administration Commands"
.SH NAME
in.stlisten \- Service Tag Listener
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
.nf
\fB/usr/lib/inet/in.stlisten\fR
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
.LP
The \fBin.stlisten\fR daemon allows a mechanism for  discovering      the  location  of  the Service Tag. By default, the \fBin.stlisten\fR daemon listens for discovery probes (using  a minimal built-in protocol) on \fBTCP\fR port 6481.
.sp
.LP
The daemon is under control of the service management facility, \fBsmf\fR(5), under its \fBinetd\fR framework.  It only runs upon demand and exits when no longer in use.
.SH ATTRIBUTES
.sp
.LP
