.TE

.SH SEE ALSO
.sp
.LP
\fBin.stdiscover\fR(1M), \fBstclient\fR(1M), \fBsvccfg\fR(1M), \fBattributes\fR(5), \fBenviron\fR(5), \fBsmf\fR(5)
.SH NOTES
.sp
.LP
In open networks where the participants may not always be trusted, it is recommended that you deploy this daemon with the \fBpassphrase-encryption\fR option. In \fBsmf\fR(5) environments, the following command can be used to set the \fIpassphrase\fR:
.sp
.in +2
.nf
< prepare a text file "passfile" containing the passphrase >
# chown svctag:daemon passfile
# chmod 600 passfile
svccfg -s svc:/network/stlisten \e
        setprop servicetag/passphrase=passfile
.fi
.in -2
.sp

.sp
.LP
where \fIpassfile\fR is the path of a file containing the intended \fIpassphrase\fR.
.sp
.LP
This \fIpassphrase\fR can be subsequently cleared as follows:
.sp
.in +2
.nf
svccfg -s svc:/network/stlisten \e
        setprop servicetag/passphrase=""
.fi
.in -2
.sp

